    explanation:
      'This patient has deficits across multiple swallowing subsystems. EMST has evidence for improving both cough function and swallowing physiology in PD by strengthening the expiratory and submental muscles. The effortful swallow addresses tongue base retraction and pharyngeal pressure. The Mendelsohn maneuver targets hyolaryngeal excursion and UES opening. Compensatory diet modifications provide safety during the rehabilitative phase. This multicomponent approach addresses the broadest range of deficits.',
