    stem: 'An SLP is treating a 6-year-old child with Down syndrome who has a phonological disorder characterized by final consonant deletion, cluster reduction, and stopping of fricatives. The child also has mild-moderate receptive-expressive language delay. Given the dual diagnosis, which treatment approach is MOST efficient?',
